column5: Any kind of file-like-structure. Reader will only return file paths. Not for use in production. Can be used as a placeholder for custom data management.
Arrays are a series of data objects, without index.
Array with additional index information for each element, that is not a datetime.
An iarray that additionally has a name property of any valid metacatalog Variable.
Array indexed by datetime information. The datetimes need to be of increasing order.
Timeseries that holds an additional Variable name to describe the content.
NDArrays are multidimensional arrays of common atomic data-type.
The named raster images are not implemented yet.
Special case of NDArray with exactly two dimensions.
NDArray with any index except datetime information.
idataframe with additional name property of any valid metacatalog Variable.
NDArray indexed by datetime information. The datetimes need to be of increasing order.
Timeseries table that holds an additional Variable name to describe the content.
